crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a Remote Access Trojan (RAT). It performs extensive system reconnaissance, including gathering OS information, user/computer names, process lists, and network configuration. It can execute remote commands via `cmd.exe`, take screenshots and encode them as JPEGs, and exfiltrates this data to a Command and Control (C2) server. It also contains unusual functionality to upload files to the VirusTotal API, likely for anti-analysis purposes. Key IOCs include the C2 domain `a6281279.yolox.net` (contacted via `/gate.php`), the use of the VT API with key `4d1ee14a3191ba1afde5261326dcd7e81793afacb6aa7e46d0b467bc6ebcd367`, and a custom encryption routine seeded with the string "VMGrab".
